description: This column contains the first names of users associated with various business accounts on the platform. It is part of the user account management system, allowing for the identification and personalization of user interactions within the platform.

This column contains the last names of users associated with accounts on the platform. It is used to identify and differentiate users within the system, aiding in user management, authentication, and personalization of interactions. The last names can also be utilized in data analytics for reporting and performance evaluations related to user engagement and business operations.
This column contains the first line of the address, which typically includes the primary information for locating a specific business or individual, such as the street name and number.

This column contains additional address information for a location, which may include details like suite numbers, apartment numbers, or any other relevant line of text that complements the main address provided in 'line_1'. It is used to provide more specificity to the address, ensuring accurate identification of the location for business operations and user interactions.

This column contains the city names associated with addresses in the database. It provides a specific location identifier for each address, which is essential for geographic categorization and serves to enhance user experience in operations such as searching, filtering, and displaying addresses on the platform. The city data supports various functionalities, including user account management and investment tracking, by allowing for a clear understanding of regional distributions and targeting.

This column contains data related to the region associated with a specific address. It serves to identify the geographical area or administrative division that is part of the overall address, which may be crucial for categorizing locations, performing regional analytics, and managing user interactions based on geographic segmentation.

This column contains postal codes associated with addresses, which serve as unique identifiers for specific geographic areas. Postal codes are essential for accurately locating and organizing addresses, enabling efficient logistics, and facilitating communication in the context of managing business operations and user accounts within the platform.

This column contains the names of the countries where the addresses are located. It is used to identify the geographical location of each address within the broader context of the platform's operations, which may involve international business transactions, user interactions, and investment opportunities.

This column contains information about the district associated with a particular address. The district serves as a geographical or administrative division within a city or region, helping to organize and categorize locations for purposes such as logistics, governance, or demographic analysis. This data is essential for understanding the address's context within the broader area and for enhancing location-based services within the business operations platform.

This column contains the region code, which is a short alphanumeric identifier that corresponds to a specific geographic region. It is used to categorize or identify the geographical area associated with the address, facilitating data organization, retrieval, and analytics within the platform managing business operations and user interactions.

It serves as a secure token that allows the client application to confirm payments on behalf of the user, ensuring that the transaction can be completed while maintaining security and preventing unauthorized access.

description: This column contains information about the user agent strings associated with authentication sessions. User agents are used to identify the operating system, browser, and device type of users accessing the platform. This data helps in analyzing user behavior, optimizing user experience, and ensuring compatibility across different platforms. The user agent information can also contribute to security measures by identifying unusual access patterns or devices.

This column is about the tags associated with authentication sessions, which may categorize or label user actions, types of access, or specific session characteristics within the platform. This can help in analyzing user behavior, session duration, and interactions during various business operations, while also aiding in data analytics and performance tracking.

This column contains the audience identifier associated with user accounts, likely used to specify or restrict the context in which the user authentication tokens are valid, ensuring that tokens are only usable within designated applications or services.

This column indicates the role of users within the platform, defining their permissions and access levels. Roles may include distinctions such as admin, investor, entrepreneur, and user, allowing for various functionalities tailored to each type of user in the context of managing business operations and interactions.
This column contains the email addresses of users registered on the platform. It is essential for user identification, communication, and serves as a unique identifier in authentication processes.

This column contains the encrypted passwords of users on the platform. It securely stores user authentication credentials by encrypting the plain text passwords, ensuring that sensitive information is not stored in an easily accessible format. This column is critical for maintaining user security and protecting against unauthorized access.

This column stores the confirmation token associated with user accounts, which is used to verify a user's email address during the registration process. The token is generated when a user signs up and sent to their email, allowing them to confirm their identity and activate their account. It plays a crucial role in the authentication and authorization processes, ensuring that only verified users can access certain functionalities within the platform.

This column stores the recovery token associated with user accounts, which is used for account recovery processes. It allows users to securely regain access to their accounts in case they forget their passwords or need to verify their identity. The recovery token is typically a unique, time-sensitive string generated to ensure that the recovery process is secure and that unauthorized access is prevented.

This column contains the token associated with a user's request to change their email address. It is utilized as part of the authentication and authorization process to verify the user's identity and ensure security when updating their email information on the platform.

This column contains information related to email changes for users, specifically storing the new email address that users wish to adopt as part of the user account management process within the platform.

This column contains the names of various ventures that are being managed within the platform. Each entry represents a unique business or investment opportunity that the platform tracks, facilitating user engagement and investment interactions.
